bilingual.source: Store the herbs in a dry place.
bilingual.target: 将草药存放在干燥的地方。

bilingual.source: The plant vive even in dry soil.
bilingual.target: 这种植物即使在干燥的土壤中也能活着。

bilingual.source: Store EtOH in a cool, dry place.
bilingual.target: 将乙醇存放在阴凉干燥的地方。

bilingual.source: Always keep matches in a dry place.
bilingual.target: 始终将火柴放在干燥的地方。

bilingual.source: You need dry tinder to make a fire.
bilingual.target: 你需要干燥的火绒来生火。

bilingual.source: Very dry air can cause a nosebleed.

bilingual.source: Store the flour in a cool, dry place.

bilingual.source: Store the liquids in a cool, dry place.

bilingual.source: Store isopropanol in a cool, dry place.

list.abstract: Dry（英[draɪ]，美[draɪ]），是英文单词，作形容词时，为干的；干爽的；不加掩饰的，作动词时，为变干；忘记台词；弄干，作名词时，为干燥过程；旱季；严格的货币主义者，例句为“The area was very dry with low rainfall because of its geographical conditions.”（由于地理条件，该地区非常干燥，降雨量很低。） Dry形容词类近义词为exsuccousthirsty，不及物动词类近义词为desiccateexsiccate，名词类近义词为dryout，反义词为wetsweetphlegmy，同根词为dried、dryish、drily。

yingyinNormal.en: Humidity is low, it's a dry night, little bit of wind to dispel the smoke, I think they gonna be in for a tremendous treat and it could start any moment now.
yingyinNormal.zh: 湿度低，干燥的夜晚，有点吹散烟雾的微风，他们会好好利用这一情况，现在演出随时。

yingyinNormal.en: Turpan, home of the Uygur people, seen from the air is a dry and desolate dessert, dotted by thousands of mysterious pock marks, holes that lead to a two-thousand-year old subterranean system, that's longer than the length of India, the Karez canal network.
yingyinNormal.zh: 吐鲁番是维吾尔族人的家园。俯瞰吐鲁番，是一片荒芜干燥的沙漠。数千个神秘的麻斑星罗棋布。这些洞是绵延至少两千多年的地下水系统，比整个印度还长——坎儿井运河系统。

yingyinNormal.en: Fingers crossed your rock surroundings will get gently lifted up by plate tectonics, sea levels will change, and you'll end up under dry land close to the surface, but not so close that erosion from wind and rain wipes you away before someone can come find you.
yingyinNormal.zh: 穿流过你周围的岩石会通过板块构造慢慢抬升，海平面会变化，你最终会在干燥的陆面下接近地表，但又不是特别近，所以在你被发现之前表层的岩石被风雨侵蚀流失。

yingyinNormal.en: Ls it dry in here?
yingyinNormal.zh: 这里是不是很干燥？

yingyinNormal.en: Okay, okay. I think it's dry.
yingyinNormal.zh: 好了，好了，这下干了。

yingyinNormal.en: There you are, Daddy Pig. Nice and dry.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你也全干了，猪爸爸，又干爽又整洁。

yingyinNormal.en: You go and dry yourselves while I polish the car.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你们去弄干衣服，我来擦擦车。

yingyinNormal.en: Now you have clean dry hands, with minimal waste.
yingyinNormal.zh: 现在，你不用浪费太多纸，就可以有干净又干爽的双手。

yingyinNormal.en: Dry-cleaning? If it's too much... If it's too late...
yingyinNormal.zh: 干洗？如果要求过分了点，又或者时间太晚...

yingyinNormal.en: Blair? Serena. Hey, I got two bone-dry caps and audrey.
yingyinNormal.zh: 布莱尔？瑟琳娜。嗨，我带了两顶棒球帽和奥瑞杂志。

yingyinNormal.en: Dry chillies are also an important ingredient in Chinese cooking.
yingyinNormal.zh: 干辣椒也是中国菜中的重要调料。

yingyinNormal.en: Oh! Sorry, Daddy Pig! Let's get you dry! There you are, Daddy Pig! Nice and dry!
yingyinNormal.zh: 噢，对不起，猪爸爸！我们把你弄干吧！好了，猪爸爸！舒爽干燥！

yingyinNormal.en: Poor Teddy. He's soaking wet. Yes, poor Teddy. Let's get him dry. Poor Teddy. There you are, Teddy. All dry.
yingyinNormal.zh: 可怜的泰迪，他全身都湿透了。是的，可怜的泰迪，我们把他弄干。可怜的泰迪，可以了，泰迪，全都干了。

yingyinNormal.en: And what do you do with dry leaves? I don't know.
yingyinNormal.zh: 那我们能拿干树叶做什么呢？我不知道。

yingyinNormal.en: This is the optimal arrangement to dry with the least amount of paper. Again, shake your hands 12 times, fold, and dry.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这是用最少量的纸，达到最佳的干手方式 再看一次，甩手12下，对折再擦干。

yingyinNormal.en: Did you wash your hands? With soap? Did you dry them?
yingyinNormal.zh: 你洗手了吗？用肥皂了吗？擦干了吗？

yingyinNormal.en: I should have marinated it longer. I hope it isn't dry.
yingyinNormal.zh: 腌制的时间应该长一点的。希望不会太干。

yingyinNormal.en: 50 years of watching those hydro rigs suck our planet dry.
yingyinNormal.zh: 50年来眼看着水能塔将地球的能源榨干。

yingyinNormal.en: Wait a minute. Yes, Joe? I forgot to pick up my dry cleaning.
yingyinNormal.zh: 等等，怎么了，乔伊? 我忘了把衣服从干洗店拿回来了。

yingyinNormal.en: Mummy! Daddy! The puddles are all dry and we can't jump in them!
yingyinNormal.zh: 妈妈！爸爸！泥水坑全都干了，我们不能在里面跳了！

examination_example.sentence: The first is the abandonment of farmland, especially in high, <highlight>dry</highlight> places where nothing grows terribly well.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 第一个是放弃农田，尤其是在高而干燥的地方，那里没有什么长得特别好的东西。

examination_example.sentence: Watch paint <highlight>dry</highlight> or water boil, or put away your smartphone for a while, and you might unlock your next big idea.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 看着油漆变干或水烧开，或者暂时收起你的智能手机，你可能会开启你的下一个伟大的想法。

examination_example.sentence: Although in-flight infections thrive in <highlight>dry</highlight> environments like airplanes, your risk of getting sick from an airplane is actually low because of the air filters used.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 尽管在飞机等干燥环境中飞行中感染很普遍，但由于使用了空气过滤器，因此在飞机上生病的风险实际上很低。

examination_example.sentence: Every time you make coffee, <highlight>dry</highlight> the leftover coffee grounds and keep them in small balls, then place the balls in the kitchen.

examination_example.sentence: Millions of acres of wetlands were <highlight>dried</highlight> to feed and house the ever-increasing populations, greatly reducing waterfowl habitat.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 数百万英亩的湿地被抽干，用来养活和安置不断增长的人口，大大减少了水禽的栖息地。

examination_example.sentence: No matter how attractive they look in the store, once I get them home they're unfailingly <highlight>dry</highlight>, hard, and tasteless.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 不管它们在店里看起来有多吸引人，一旦我把它们带回家，它们就会永远干枯、坚硬、无味。

examination_example.sentence: Instead, <highlight>dry</highlight> winds from the desert keep the clouds away at night.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 相反，来自沙漠的干燥的风在夜间阻挡了云层。

examination_example.sentence: Meanwhile in Europe, crops in the northwest are suffering the <highlight>driest</highlight> weather in the past 80 years.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 与此同时，在欧洲，西北部的农作物正遭受着80年来最干旱的天气。

examination_example.sentence: Food can be kept for a long time in the north, as it is usually cold and <highlight>dry</highlight> there.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 食物在北方可以保存很长时间，因为那里通常寒冷而干燥。

examination_example.sentence: After being <highlight>dried</highlight> for a long time in the fire, our gifts for teachers were ready.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 在火中烘干许久过后，我们送给老师的礼物也就准备好了。

examination_example.sentence: On the one hand, the elephants’ main lake, their only water source (来源), <highlight>dried</highlight> up.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 一方面，大象们唯一的水源——主湖枯竭了。

examination_example.sentence: After a while she said, "Alice! Stop crying! Crying doesn't help! <highlight>Dry</highlight> your tears immediately!"
examination_example.sentence_trans: 过了一会儿，她说：“爱丽丝，别哭了！哭没有用！赶快擦干眼泪！”
